The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 600) Combines video from the historic Bob 

 Marley and the Wailers 1977 London performance with a documentary 

 on the reggae-king called Caribbean Nights. Besides 

 classics such as I shot the sheriff, No woman 

 no cry, Jammin?, Get up stand up and Exodus, 

 there are digitally enhance footage and exclusive new tracks. 

 THE TRIBUTE

 (Srijan rooftop, 6 pm-9 pm, April 14) A salute to sarod 

 maestro Ali Akbar Khan on his 83rd birthday. The show, crafted 

 by sarod exponent Anindya Banerjee, will present his recordings 

 and also trace the musician?s journey from Maihar to Lucknow, 

 Jodhpur to San Francisco. 

 THE DISPLAY

 (Galerie 

 88, 3 pm to 7 pm, from April 9) The collection showcases how 

 Manish Pushkale creates images epitomising the minimalist 

 mode. The artist has researched on Jain Thirthankaras and 

 has worked in the print media in Bhopal. 




